NOTICE - (regarding itemID, and dpChain)
You'll notice that a lot of the methods in this component use two parameters: dpChain, and itemID. Basically, these two parameters serve to point to a menu item. If you didn't understood these two parameters very well, you may have to look at the posInfo object in the items movie clips.

In each menu item, there is an object called posInfo, that holds two properties: dpChain, and itemID.

So, if you want to know each dpChain, and itemID for a menu item, you simply write (Assuming that you have an instance of the Hierarchical Menu component on stage called "my_hm"):




my_hm.onPressItem = function(item) {

    trace("item : " + item.data.name);

    for(var posProp in item.posInfo) {

        trace(posProp + " = " + item.posInfo[posProp]);

    }

    trace("-------------");

}


then, choose Control > Test Movie, and when you press with the mouse a menu item, you"ll notice a message in the Output Window, that shows both the dpChain, and the itemID for the item you pressed on.
